Four Corvus corax were seen at this location, possibly two mated pairs fighting over territory. This noise and along with a low "coh" was spotted. I could not get a good photo of either pair since they were a distance away.

LOCATION INFORMATION
•Take I-5 N from Olympia, WA to exit 118 in Dupont, WA. Follow Center Drive for 1.5 miles and turn left towards Sequalitchew Creek Trailhead. Sighting of the Ravens was on the beach at the very end of the trail just before and also after the train tunnel. 

HABITAT INFORMATION
• Dense forest, dominant overstory trees change from coniferous to deciduous and back frequently along the trail. 
Overstory: Pseudotsuga menzesii, corylus cornuta, Acer macrophyllum. Unserstory: Miner's lettuce, trailing blackberries, polystichum munitum, small thuja plicata

CLIMATE INFORMATION
• 0% cloud cover
• Sunshine
• 79 degrees
• no wind below tree canopy
